(88, 1, 'What is Global Distribution System and how it works', 'what-is-global-distribution-system-and-how-it-works', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The internet and eCommerce have made our lives extremely easy for us. Contributing even more to our ease are networks like GDS, Global Distribution Systems. Back in the 1960s, there were not many efficient ways to keep track and conduct business with organizations or people with geographical constraints. That is when it was felt that a more efficient method was required. The development and usage of global distribution systems started in the 1970s. That is when B2B commerce started between organizations and travel agencies felt that a better system was required for them to work effectively and fully serve their purpose.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">&nbsp;The global distribution system can be defined as a network that helps with the connectivity of different travel agencies to multiple different organizations such as hotels. It also greatly helps with making reservations and booking different flights according to the clients&rsquo; requirements. These systems allow the travel agencies to have access to hotel inventories that can greatly help them with making different bookings according to what the client is looking for. For example, Global distribution systems help the airline to keep track of the types of rooms available in different hotels, for example, the number of luxury rooms, suites and regular rooms available in hotels that are situated in different geographical locations. That is because Global Distribution Systems help the travel agencies with being updated with the latest information available about different hotels, airlines, and tours.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Global distribution systems have not only made the lives of travel agencies easier, but it has also helped them to capture more business and reaching out even more to their potential clients. Because of the multiple benefits that are offered by these systems, they are mostly used by travel agencies. These systems have greatly changed the way the travel agencies have started operating, that is because the factor of specificity has been included and the travel agencies know when, where and how to provide their services to a large pool of different clients at once. This also helps them save time. It has also helped to maximize the number of bookings of their clients which also indirectly helps the travel agencies to generate more revenues. These systems are not only beneficial to the travel agencies but also to the hotels. That is because it helps them to attract more customers. Hotels do that because of easy accessibility to the travel agencies. This also helps the hotels to generate more revenues, hence more profits. Another major advantage of using these systems in conducting business activities is that they do not require any lengthy contracts or any major formalities that need to be performed. They also help the travel agencies target extremely specific markets and tap unexplored markets if that is one of their aims or objectives.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Another major change the GDS has brought about in the word of travel agencies is that it helps them capture more corporate level clients and businessmen who are always on the go. That is because people generally find it hard to take care of bookings and their traveling schedules so they seek the help of travel agencies to do that. It is also thought to be easier for the client as they believe that they end up saving money by hiring a travel agency to do all the work for them.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The benefits of using global distribution systems are never-ending, however, there is also some drawback that should be taken into consideration by the organizations employing these systems. The biggest drawback of using these systems is the initial cost. In the case of hotels and travel agencies, hotels usually pay and initial fees and then over a period of time, it pays the agent and the transaction fees depending on the bookings that are being done. The fees can be both high or low however it is important for hotels to make sure that their prices are not too high and that they are balanced rates considering the type of market in which they are operating. Good prices being set by hotels is the key to developing a good relationship with the travel agency. However, it is also important for the hotels to make sure that they don&rsquo;t set their prices too low in an attempt to capture or attract more customers because that will eventually negatively affect the profits being generated by the hotels to a great extent.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">There are three main types of global distributions systems</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Amadues GDS &ndash; This type of system is the market leader as it enjoys a good 40 percent of its market shares. It has been operating for more than 30 years in the world of global distribution systems, it operates in more than 190 markets and it has more than 17000 employees working for it. It has an extremely high level of access to the European markets and its headquarters are situated in Germany. This type of system is usually used by travel agencies to book flights.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Sabre GDS &ndash; This type of system is the closest competitor of Amadues GDS. It is mostly used by hotels as it caters to their requirements in aiding the hotels with making reservations and bookings. This system is used by more than 200,000 hotels and it not only helps with the reservations but it also provides multiple hotel tech solutions. Its database is located in US Texas.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Travelport GDS &ndash; This system has three main subdivisions; Apollo, Worldspam and Galileo. This system was developed in 1971 and it caters to very large and very diverse markets of Asia, The United States, and Europe. Along with the basic service, it also provides a variety of travel industry solutions. Galileo was developed for catering to the needs of hotels whereas Worldspam was developed specifically for airlines.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">An intermediary is required for the efficient functioning of a GDS. That means that a GDS provider, the intermediary, will provide the GDS system to the organization. The intermediary also has access to the property management system of the organization. For example, in the case of a hotel, the hotel will be able to manage all of its details for example its photos, rates, descriptions, room listings and the services that are offered. This is helpful because it leads to the efficient management of the inventory. As reservations are made, it shows that the inventory has reduced across all channels along with the official website of the hotel itself.</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\nLooking at your online solution to sell your GDS tickets or suppliers&#39; integration?&nbsp;<br />\r\ncontact us today at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://phptravels.com/\">https://phptravels.com/</a>&nbsp;and we will help you to integrate your GDS with your website and mobile apps.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Global Distribution System, travel agencies, bookings, easy accessibility', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e32bf26a38a1.jpg', 3098, '2020-01-29 21:55:03'),
(91, 1, 'Role played by Instagram to help a travel agency acquire new customers', 'role-played-by-instagram-to-help-a-travel-agency-acquire-new-customers', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">We are currently living in a world that is constantly offering us new opportunities. Not only the opportunities, connecting with other people in today&#39;s&nbsp;era is a very easy thing to do. With the internet and multiple social media platforms available, we can easily connect with others and share our lives with them without much hassle. Not only on a personal level, but this has helped businesses to expand and reach out to new people as well.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Instagram is a platform that is currently playing a major role in different business sectors. When we talk about a travel agency, Instagram can play a major role in helping to explore new customers and reach out to the untapped markets. The first and the most important thing that a travel agency must do is create an Instagram profile and make sure that it is public so that it is easy for people to visit that profile. Another thing that should be kept in mind is that people are only going to know more about your travel agency if you keep posting about it so it is essential to keep the masses updated. If we compare Instagram to other social media platforms, a very different feature of Instagram is that as we increase the number of hashtags under the posts, it is most likely to appear more often on other peoples&rsquo; profiles &ndash; that is a very effective technique that can be used to attract new client towards your travel agency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">It is important to make sure that your Instagram profile is visually attractive so it is essential to post attractive pictures of different travel destinations to inspire people to travel more and hence, use the services provided by your travel agency. To make the pictures even more attractive and visually appealing, Instagram provides a wide range of filters that can be used to enhance the colors and the overall aesthetic of the picture. Along with uploading attractive pictures, it is important to write a good caption under it. The caption can include details of the location along with some interesting facts about its history and culture. This helps the reader to explore different perspectives of traveling. Moreover, it can also prove to be beneficial to add different locations on the posts, that way a company can make its position on the map.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">At the end of the day, all the effort that is being put into these posts will go into waste if there is no engagement from the client. People, these days, are always very excited to share their life updates with their loved ones through social media and people, generally, tend to post more when they are on vacation so a good way of seeking customer attention can be to hold a &lsquo;best picture competition&rsquo;. The followers of your account will upload different pictures and tag you under their posts. The person with the best image of a unique travel destination can be offered something as a reward. This will help to increase the level of participation and engagement of the people. The travel agency can also ask their clients to use hashtags under their posts and tag them.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">We are living in a world in which everything is digitized so it is important to keep up with the latest trends and do the marketing of your products or services through digital means. This can be done through the building and designing of digital brochures and pamphlets. People usually find bright colors and bold fonts to be very attractive and eye-catching so they can be used to make your digital advertisement visually attractive.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The young generation of today is very well aware of all the digital platforms that are available to them. In fact, a study showed that 53 percent of our population of ages between 18 to 29 have their own Instagram accounts. So, it can prove to be beneficial for a travel agency to target today&#39;s&rsquo; youth and reach out to them. Not only because they have their own personal Instagram accounts, but today&#39;s&rsquo; youth is also very interested in traveling and exploring new places on Earth so targeting them specifically and marketing your product/service to them can prove to be extremely beneficial. It can also result in positive word of mouth of your company.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">There is a large number of bloggers and influencers on Instagram whom people trust. Travel agencies can also reach out to them for paid or unpaid collaborations. Usually, bloggers with a large number of following don&rsquo;t collaborate with brands unless they are paid but bloggers with a small following don&rsquo;t mind unpaid collaborations as they believe that they are still growing and any collaboration can help them in their journey of growth. Travel agencies can ask bloggers to post pictures of different tourist attractions and tag them under these posts. This can prove to be beneficial for the travel agency because people find it much easier to relate to the bloggers on a personal level and trust them rather than being convinced by the organization that is advertising its products/services itself. If a travel agency does not have enough budget for collaboration, then they can follow back their followers from their official Instagram account and share the pictures of their followers on their Instagram stories to show appreciation and recognition.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Despite such a positive role being played by Instagram to capture more clients, there is however a big barrier to this social media platform that can cause problems for travel agencies. That is, Instagram prioritizes only those posts which a person seems to be interested in and stops showing the posts that are not of the users&rsquo; interest. A good way to overcome is this problem can be to share all your posts on Facebook, as it is the parent company of Instagram, to increase the viewership of your content.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Considering the wide variety of social media platforms available, Instagram can prove to be the most efficient way of communicating and attracting new customers. That is because Instagram usage has drastically increased over the years as compared to other social media platforms, such as Facebook, which has made it even easier to approach the masses.</span></p>\r\n', '', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e3817febc642.jpg', 2077, '2020-02-03 12:52:38'),
(92, 1, 'PHPTRAVELS v7.3 Released ', 'phptravels-v73-released', '<p><strong>PHPTRAVELS v7.3</strong><br />\r\nYou might have heard us talking about how we&rsquo;re changing at&nbsp;<strong>PHPTRAVELS</strong>. Well today we&rsquo;re proud to unveil our new version. It&rsquo;s more than just a fresh coat of paint though. It&rsquo;s our way of telling everyone we work with, and the wider world, who we are, what we stand for and where we&rsquo;re going. We&rsquo;ve got a bold new mission and we&rsquo;re excited to share it with you. Because you&rsquo;ve been part of our success over the years and you&rsquo;re very much part of our future.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PHPTRAVELS Mission.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve always been committed to driving innovation in the market by working closely with our network of partners. Now we are proud to have a look and logo that represents our values and a mission to lead the global transformation to modern and sustainable travel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>What does this mean for me?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PHPTRAVELS&nbsp;</strong>strategic direction and vision for the future remains focused on providing travelers with outstanding choice, convenience and service from partners in flights, hotels and car hire. By continuing to work closely with you we aim to meet and exceed traveler expectations in a market that is increasingly driven by speed and ease of booking. If you currently display any&nbsp;<strong>PHPTRAVELS&nbsp;</strong>branding on your website, we would ask that you update it with our new brand version that you can find here.<br />\r\nin your client area at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.phptravels.org/\">https://www.phptravels.org</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Version v7.3 &nbsp;- FEB &nbsp;10&nbsp;2020</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>CMS dynamic menus option enabled</li>\r\n	<li>Admin blog design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin flights page design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin hotels design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin tours design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin cars design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin offers design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin coupons design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin cms pages design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin settings page design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin supplier accounts design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin email templates design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin modules design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Admin data tables design improved and optimised</li>\r\n	<li>htaccess warning added to root</li>\r\n	<li>New feature added to edit the position of menus</li>\r\n	<li>Upgraded PHP now officially we support PHP version 7.4</li>\r\n	<li>Travelpayouts Hotels improved integration with better functionality</li>\r\n	<li>HTTPS redirection implemented by default no need to configure anymore</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed multiple rows for availability of rooms availability feature</li>\r\n	<li>Frontend flights selection design improved</li>\r\n	<li>Frontend URL Copy feature added for hotels tours and cars</li>\r\n	<li>Tours module added option to deleted selected location</li>\r\n	<li>Suppliers added commission feature</li>\r\n	<li>Email template new design implemented</li>\r\n	<li>Added discount option for hotels tours and cars</li>\r\n	<li>Widgets feature implemented for tour operators now they can share iframe</li>\r\n	<li>Complete delete all selected contents on back-end dynamically</li>\r\n	<li>Ban by IP featured added to ban any IPs for security measures</li>\r\n	<li>Added by default robot.txt for search engines improvement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 1, 2, 0, 'image_750x_5e39e7e09512f.jpg', 2333, '2020-02-12 21:31:58'),
(93, 1, 'The ultimate guide for selecting the best software suited for your online travel agency.', 'the-ultimate-guide-for-selecting-the-best-software-suited-for-your-online-travel-agency', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">In the past few decades, a lot of change has been experienced and observed in the world of travel agencies. In the previous decades, people used to do all the effort themselves whenever they wanted to go for a trip. That required days and days of endless research about different hotels, airlines, routes, etc. Not only did all of that research take up a lot of time but it also resulted in a lot of money being spent on unnecessary things. With a wide variety of travel agencies evolving over the decades, a lot of time and money of the people has been saved. The best part was that the travel agencies started taking care of all the worries of their clients and all that was left for them to worry about was to have a great vacation. A research that was conducted showed that by hiring a good travel agency that can efficiently cater to their needs, a person can save up to 452 dollars per trip, which is a lot of money for an average person who belongs to an upper middle class. Another study showed that 65 percent of people choose to make their bookings through a travel agency even if they believe online bookings to be cheaper as compared to the services provided by travel agencies.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Along with the large variety of travel agencies available for us to pick from, there is also a very wide variety of software in the market with different price tags on them. These software help travel agencies by providing their services more effectively and efficiently. However, because of the large variety, it gets really difficult for travel agencies to analyze their requirements and select the correct software for themselves. The basic idea of having software within your travel agency should be that the software should be able to manage multiple different agreements at one time and it should provide the best possible solutions to the problems that may arise within a travel agency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Choosing the correct software for your travel agency is a massive responsibility. That is because many different factors need to be taken under consideration such as where your travel agency is currently standing in the market, its long term and short term goals and objectives and most importantly, the budget that your travel agency wants to allocate towards the desired software. When we talk about the goals of your travel agency, it should be kept in mind all the possibilities of investment that might be offered to it in the future and the level of business growth that it might experience. We should also consider the type of market that they may want to cater to. For example, if a travel agency only caters to the needs of people who want to get their flights booked then they might be missing out on the large demand of clients who are looking for hotel reservations. The best thing, in that case, would be to get a software that caters to all the basic needs of a travel agency &ndash; that includes hotel reservations &ndash; but mainly focuses on flight bookings.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">People generally have the perception that the price tag on something is directly proportional to the quality that it may deliver, however, that is not always the case. If we talk about software, the most important thing that should be taken into consideration is the needs and requirements of the travel agency that software may or may not be able to fulfill. On the other hand, the best-suited software for your travel agency will also not come for free so thinking that getting software with a really low price tag would serve the purpose would not be necessarily correct as it may end up creating even more problems for your travel agency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">There is a wide variety of software out there that are specifically designed for travel agencies. If a travel agency is looking for a software that specifically revolves around booking and reservations, some of the good examples may include </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Lemax</span></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Dolphin</span></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Bookinglayer</span></strong></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.phptravels.com\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">PHPTRAVELS</span></strong></a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">These&nbsp;softwares provide&nbsp;some really interesting features like an automatic billing system, GDS connectivity, adding custom discounts and offers, online booking confirmations and much more. This software also supports multiple currencies that can help create new customers in different parts of the world and each client has its portal. They are also good at keeping all the information updated for the convenience of the client.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">For a travel agency that needs software to fulfill their accounting needs, they may want to consider Xero, TravelWorks, and OnlineInvoices as their options. This software is great with generating online invoices, managing and keeping track of the inventory, connecting to different banks and reconciling with them. They also help to keep all the data secure within an organization and help analyze the sales. Some other features of this software can include keeping track of the sales commission of each of the travel agents and the levels of employee performance.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">For tour building, Tripcreator, Tourwriter, and Orioly are really good options as they keep all the confirmations and keep all the insights and reports updated. Lastly, managing the customer relationships within an organization is also very important and some softwares are specifically designed for serving that purpose as well. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">These software include </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Zoho Travels Agency CRM</span></strong></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">LeadSquared Travel CRM</span></strong></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Kapture Travel CRM</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">This software provides features like customization of dashboards, creating travel-specific categories for the customers, supporting different marketing channels and creating an integrated set of marketing tools.</span></p>\r\n', 'travel software guide, best travel agencies software, booking software, booking engine suggestions , The ultimate guide for selecting the best software suited for your online travel agency.', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e3c00f0eea5c.jpg', 1923, '2020-02-06 12:02:54'),
(94, 1, 'How to boost your travel agency with vlogging.', 'how-to-boost-your-travel-agency-with-vlogging', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Living in a digitized world, we often come across different concepts like blogs and vlogs. Vlogging is an activity in which a person keeps a record of their daily life by making different videos. These videos can be both short or long depending on the interests of the vlogger and the type of content he or she likes to create and share. After these videos have been successfully made and edited, they are usually uploaded on a social media platform, for example, Instagram, Facebook or YouTube that is kept public for others to view. Vloggers usually tend to set a particular theme of the videos that they make and it is really important to set that particular theme because it sets the entire tone for the video but most importantly, it differentiates that one vlogger from so many other vloggers out there. Some of the examples of these themes include food, fashion, makeup, lifestyle, social issues, education, and travel. Making travel-related vlogs can sometimes turn out to be a really big challenge for the vloggers because as compared to food or maybe lifestyle, a travel vlogger has to make sure that he or she is not restricted to one particular geographical area. After all, making travel vlogs is all about exploring new destinations and keeping your viewers updated and entertained. Travel vlogs can also sometimes result in the vlogger being emotionally, physically and financially exhausted because the vlogger is always on the go. However, travel vlogs can help different travel agencies generate more business.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The vlogging industry is getting bigger day by day and people generally believe bloggers and vloggers because they believe that they are authentic and the fact that what they are saying is the truth. Since people tend to rely upon what these vloggers say, they end up making their decisions on the experience of the vlogger. People tend to watch travel vlogs because they want to hear real-life stories of the vlogger, they want to know about the reviews of different travel destinations, they want to learn about different experiences of the vlogger or they want to get a general idea of that particular travel destination before actually visiting the place themselves. This also helps the vlogger in growing their page because they end up getting a greater number of likes, comments, shares, and subscriptions. A study conducted recently showed that travel vlogs get four more times the engagement as compared to a regular vlog. Another study that was conducted showed that 48 percent of the people who are looking for different travel destinations get their ideas through Instagram posts and 52 percent of them get their ideas from Facebook posts that are shared by their friends. This is a positive thing for the travel agencies because more the people want to travel, the more they will reach out to travel agencies to finalize their trip and take care of all the little things like flights, bookings and hotel reservations.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Travel vlogs can be further classified for example some vloggers make videos about different exotic regions of the world, for example, Egypt, some vloggers may make videos about the hustle and bustle, and the busy lifestyle of all the big cities of the world, for example, New York or Lahore. Further categories can include making videos about different cultures and exploring new cuisines, for example, going for a wine tasting in Italy or making videos about experiencing risky adventures, for example, going for sky diving. These sub-categories help the viewer to make a better decision when planning out their trip.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The high-quality videos made by the travel vloggers usually highlight different cultures, histories, fashions, and trends over the globe, they also help a person decide which hotel they want to stay in or which airline they want to book for their flights. After such decisions have been made and the customer decides to reach out to a travel agency, it may eventually help in creating positive word of mouth for the travel agency itself as the customer will be satisfied with their trip as he/she knew exactly what they wanted from their trip. This also helps create a massive advantage for the travel agency to plan the trip for their client exactly the way they want which can help to avoid all those little things that can potentially create inconveniences for their customers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Sometimes travel agencies collaborate with different vloggers. That helps them to indirectly advertise their travel agency through that vlogger. For example, if a vlogger posts an interesting video on YouTube about a particular travel destination and at the end of the video talks a little about the travel agency and puts up their logo, all the people who will view that video will consider availing the services being offered by that particular travel agency. This can help the travel agency with getting more clients and creating healthy, long term relationship with them. This can also help the travel agency to create more brand awareness in the market about themselves and help it to explore new untapped markets and attract potential customers. This will give the travel agency a competitive edge. Travel vlogs can also indirectly help travel agencies with promoting new travel destinations. As they promote new travel destinations, their clients will feel inclined towards exploring them and hence availing the services being offered by the travel agency.</span></p>\r\n', 'travel agency boost, vlogging travel, vlogging agency, travel vlogging', 1, 1, 0, 'image_750x_5e58f08b4776c.jpg', 1285, '2020-02-28 12:21:20'),
(95, 1, 'Different ways to expand and grow your travel agency business.', 'different-ways-to-expand-and-grow-your-travel-agency-business', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Travel agencies have made our lives easier &ndash; from making different hotel reservations to booking different flights for us, they take care of everything. All that is left for us to do is to make the payment and make sure that we enjoy our trip. Hiring a travel agent also leads to some extra money and effort being saved as they know exactly what their client needs and that helps them to come up with the most convenient package for the client. Travel agencies make our lives easier and it seems to us that it is really easy for them to make money from us as their clients. This is not always true because like any other business, sometimes travel agencies can also have trouble with expanding their business in terms of sales, the number of customers and in terms of geographical regions. Some major factors travel agencies need to take into consideration that can help them in boosting and growing their business as a whole.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">First and foremost, every business should know what it is competing against. For a travel agency, it is important to keep track of all the competing travel agencies in the market, the services they are providing, their market share and the prices that they are offering to their clients. Knowing all of this information can help a travel agency to come up with different strategies that can help, if not beat its competition, then to at least come up to its level. It&rsquo;s also important that you know the area in which your travel agency specializes. This way more effort can be put into that specific area of your travel agency which can help to make the services even better. Almost every travel agency can perform the basic tasks for their clients like booking flights and making hotel reservations but having a special quality or a skill which you are good at can give you an edge over your competition.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Another technique that can help your travel agency to expand and grow can be by giving it a personal touch and personalizing some of the services that you are providing to your customers. It is important to make sure that you are in constant contact with your customers and that you happily answer all their questions, queries and concerns in a positive manner. Make sure that all the calls and emails are being answered timely. This helps the customer to think that they are in good hands and that the money that they are paying for the services is not being wasted. Another plus point of good communication can be the positive word of mouth for the travel agency which can be extremely beneficial in the long run. This will also gradually build up the customers&#39; confidence and increase the level of customer loyalty as they will always come to you whenever they feel the need of availing your services.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The way you market the services or the products that you are offering also makes a big difference in the level of growth or expansion that your company might experience. Nowadays, everything can be done on the internet which can be of massive advantage to the travel agencies if used correctly. It is important that the correct platforms are being used to attract the correct kind of clients for your travel agency. These days, Instagram and Facebook are two of the social media platforms that are being widely used to promote and advertise different products and services that are being offered by different organizations. Such social media platforms can also be used by travel agencies for their benefit.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">No matter what it takes, it is important to keep the standard and the quality of the services being provided by the travel agency high. This is important because no matter how much you charge your clients, people are only going to return to you to avail your services again if they have had a good experience during the first time. It is also important to make sure that only those people, representing the travel agency, are in direct contact with the customer who is good at negotiation. That is because at the end of the day all of your efforts will go to waste if you are unable to convince your potential customer to avail of your services.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">When it comes to expanding your travel agency geographically, the best and the most effective way of doing that would be to increase the number of people who represent your travel agency and make sure that they are scattered in different geographical areas and not concentrated in one particular area. That way, your representatives in different geographical locations will have someone to offer the services of the travel agency on a personal level. Another effective way of geographical expansion can be opening different offices in areas where there is high demand so that people can come and personally visit your office. This will also create a positive impression of your organization on the client as the client will be able to physically see where all the work is done.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">In a world that is constantly changing in one way or another, there is an endless number of possibilities that one could explore and avail. As a travel agent, it is important to make sure that you are updated with all the needs of your current and potential customers. Not only that it is also important to come up with new and innovative ways to meet the expectations of your customers in a way that is not too expensive for the travel agency and the customer is satisfied as well. A good way of doing that would be to hire new and experienced resources that are well aware of the latest opportunities and threats in the market. Along with new resources, the latest technology can also be hired to find out about what is going on in the market and those changes can be used in your benefit &ndash; to grow and expand your travel agency.</span></p>\r\n', 'easy travel agency, different hotel reservation, booking hotel easy, easy booking hotel, easy agency, easy travel', 1, 1, 0, 'image_750x_5e57952ee1ea8.jpg', 1293, '2020-02-27 12:21:57'),
(96, 1, 'Why is it important to keep your travel agency multilingual and multi-currency', 'why-is-it-important-to-keep-your-travel-agency-multilingual-and-multi-currency', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">There are approximately 6500 languages in this world and many more speakers of those languages. When we talk about currencies, there are currently 164 different currencies that are being used all over the world. Having a business that offers its services in multiple different languages in exchange for many different currencies means that your business will be able to capture a lot more people who speak different languages and use multiple currencies in different parts of the world. One of the biggest barriers of communication is the language barrier and overcoming this hurdle means that you may be able to generate a lot more business and attract a lot more customers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Operating a travel agency that can provide their services in different languages can have a great impact on your customer service and can help you generate a lot more revenue. Being able to read and comprehend things clearly can have a big impact on the customers&rsquo; decision before making a purchase, the same is the case with travel agencies. A study showed that there are more chances for a customer to purchase your product or avail the service being offered if the information provided on your website is in their native language. Easy comprehension is not the only benefit that comes with a multilingual company, another major advantage is that your client finds it easier to trust your company and is easily convinced that your company is legitimate and is a credible source for information. Moreover, the need for multilingual online booking engines has been on a rise over the past few decades so having a multilingual website can help cater to that particular need as well as helping in generating more business for the travel agency. Google translate can be of help to a certain extent but there is no comparison between a machine-translated website and a website that has been optimized from the very beginning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">In the beginning, the idea of developing a multilingual website can be a little hard to comprehend since there are approximately 6500 languages. Because of the large variety of languages, it can be a little intimidating when deciding on which language to chose and which not to prioritize. An easy way to make that decision can be to use different tools and software are to find out where most of your clients are coming from. Then, according to those different regions and areas, more languages can be incorporated into your website. Having a multilingual website is extremely important for those travel agencies that market their services on an international level. That is because if your website is multilingual, it will most likely appear at the top when multilingual travel agencies are searched on different search engines which will automatically boost the traffic on your website as it will be of service to more people.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Having a multilingual website without options of different currencies won&rsquo;t be of much use. For example, if your search engine has the options of Hindi, Urdu, and English as languages but the transactions can only be made in US dollar, then you are likely to lose clients who speak Hindi or Urdu as they won&rsquo;t have a model through which they can make a payment. So, your clients must have the option of making a payment through the currency of that particular area of which language is being used. A big advantage of operating a multi-currency website is the convenience of your client. It is really important to make things easy and understandable for your client. That way, whenever your client feels the need to avail of the services of a travel agency, they will automatically feel inclined towards your agency. This will, eventually, increase customer loyalty as being transparent about your rates and prices is the key to more loyal customers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Having a multi-currency website means that your travel agency can easily attract more customers from international markets. This can help your travel agency to explore many different markets and gain more business. As a result, this can lead to higher levels of profitability of your travel agency both in the short and long run. People also appreciate consistency in the prices that are mentioned. Consistency in prices makes the client feel as if they are saving money by availing your services rather than going for a travel agency that only offers payment through one currency. Having a multi-currency travel agency also means that your customer will have more options when it comes to making the payment which results in further convenience for the customer. People also feel that by making the payment in a different currency, they are availing the same benefit for a lower cost as compared to making a payment in their currency.</span></p>\r\n', 'travel agency multi language, travel agency multi currency, multi language and current travel agency, multiple languages and currencies travel company', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e551e6d51b06.jpg', 1237, '2020-02-25 12:23:16');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `status`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `keywords`, `user_id`, `category_id`, `subcategory_id`, `img`, `hits`, `created_at`) VALUES
(97, 1, 'How is travel technology evolving and boosting the travel industry', 'how-is-travel-technology-evolving-and-boosting-the-travel-industry', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The technological advancements around us are increasing day and day. The technology around us is taking new twists and turns almost every other day leaving a great impact on our lives and leaving us baffled. Earlier, what was considered impossible is now very common in our lives. Not only have all the technological advancements made an impact on our lives, but it has also made a massive impact on the tourism industry in a positive way. Technology has done some pretty amazing stuff in the past few years and has made the life of travel agents extremely easy. From surveying and planning your trip to booking, traveling and experiencing, technology has made all of it easy for us to do. According to one of the studies conducted, it has been observed that more than 50 million people traveled in 2015 as compared to 2014. This drastic increase over just a year is because of the technological advancements and the ease that it has resulted.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">One of the biggest advantages of all these technological advancements around us that we, as consumers, can look up for anything that we want thanks to the wide internet availability. All sorts of information are readily available for us and we can attain the knowledge of anything in a matter of just a few seconds. Because of this, it can be said that information technology is what is holding the tourism business in its place. Because of so much information available around us, the levels of awareness in people have increased. Nowadays, people are more informed about the latest tourist destinations and different places on earth that are attractive for people who love to travel and are adventurous. Because of this, the demand for travel agencies has also increased hence increasing the amounts of average annual revenue generated for the travel agencies by large numbers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Another thing that has made the process of decision making easier consumers is the invention of smartphones. Nowadays, people think of their smartphones as their best friend, they always have their smartphones with them which means that they can easily access any sort of information that they desire. People tend to feel incomplete if they don&rsquo;t have their phones with them. Because of such great attachment to a device that can readily inform you with anything, the task of planning out different vacations and coordinating with their travel agents has been made a lot easier for the people. Smartphones have another major advantage because of which they are often not given enough credit for making our lives easier, which is the ease in communicating efficiently and effectively with multiple people at the same time.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Because of the large variety of online travel portals and online travel agencies, it is a lot easier for people to decide which portal or agency is the best suited for their needs and requirements, as it has been famously quoted, &lsquo;time is money&rsquo;. Because of the high level of engagement on multiple different social media platforms, the decision-making process of the consumer has been made even easier. That is because people can use different social media platforms such as Instagram or Facebook the acknowledge themselves about the different experiences of people with different travel agencies. This can help them to make their final decision as to which travel agency they should approach based on the reviews that they read online. Along with customers, travel agencies can also benefit from these social media platforms. These social media platforms can be used by travel agencies to approach new/potential customers by placing their advertisements on these platforms. These platforms are not only beneficial when a travel agency is attempting to capture new customers, but they can also be used to help rotate a positive image of the travel agency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Technology can also help in rapid communication between the client and the travel agency. For example, if there is a sudden change of plans from the consumer&#39;s side, he can easily communicate with his travel agent about those changes without having to go through any major inconveniences. This is also an advantage for the travel agency, for example, if there is any problem with booking the flights, making the hotel reservations or planning out the tours, the travel agency can easily communicate to their client about these inconveniences and provide them with other alternative solutions that suit the client. The advancements in technology have also helped the travel agencies to develop a healthier relationship with their stakeholders such as different people operating at different levels within their business network, mainly because of better communication.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Technological advancements have also made things easier for hotels. Check-ins and check-outs can be done in a matter of a few seconds without having the customer go through any major inconvenience and ruining their experience for them. Different travel agencies and hotels have installed multiple different software that helps them in attaining their main goal and purpose. Not only are these software&rsquo; easy to use, but they are also extremely accurate and have extremely high speed. Some software does have a big price tag on them but, if we consider the long run, they are a good investment. This software can store all sorts of information; hotel staff, housekeeping, preferences of the guests, levels of inventories, details about the reservations, details about the flights and much more. Having so much information stored that can be made available to a person in a matter of seconds has made the lives of the people working in the tourism sector and the lives of the clients much easier.</span></p>\r\n', 'travel technology,  travel agency, travel industry, travel boosting industry', 1, 1, 0, 'image_750x_5e515a68c528b.jpg', 1365, '2020-02-22 12:29:40'),
(98, 1, 'How to transform a physical travel agency into an online travel agency', 'how-to-transform-a-physical-travel-agency-into-an-online-travel-agency', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Coming up with an online version of your already existing travel agency can be a big step for your entire brand. It can help your business expand and grow into many different directions that can eventually lead to more profitability. Starting an online version of your travel agency can be a lot easier if you compare it to opening and establishing a physical travel agency. The main reason for that can be that you do not have to look for an actual physical place where you can develop a working environment for yourself and your employees, everything can be done from your computers while remaining in your very own comfort zone. This can also help to save up some extra expenses and useful resources that can be invested in your travel agency. Working with an online travel agency can also be a lot easier for your stakeholders as they would not have to physically meet you every single time, this can help to save up some time as well.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Because of the constantly increasing levels of demand for good and well-experienced travel agents, it will be very easy to develop an online version of your travel agency and generate demand for the services that you are offering. However, there are a few factors that need to be kept in mind when you are planning on marking an online presence through your travel agency. The first and the most important factor that should be taken into consideration when opening an online version of an organization is the level of pre-planning that you require. You need to plan out every tiny detail about your travel agency so that you can avoid facing any problems later on. Factors like different categories available on your website or the basic outlook of your website can be some of the examples of the details that you need to take care of. You also need to think about the cut-throat competition in the tourism market so that you can come up with different strategies that can help you run the online version of your travel agency successfully. The best way to deal with high levels of competition in the market is to come up with a very straight forward strategy that is also realistic. You also need to make the advancements in the online world step-by-step and not rush into things all at once.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">It is also important to know your audience and target market well. You should have all the knowledge about the people you are trying to attract for your online travel agency. To attract them and gain their trust, you should make sure that your travel agency has some of the qualities that can help you stand out from your competition. A major advantage for you can be that you have an online as well as a physical travel agency, that way your customer will have the option of choosing whichever one he/she is more comfortable with. One of the best ways to know your target audience is by interacting and communicating with people. The more you know about what people want or what troubles them, the better you will be able to provide your services. For example, knowing the past experiences of your potential customers with other travel agencies can help you understand them a little better and know more about their likes and dislikes.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Using a host agency for your online travel agency can also be another intelligent decision that you make. Not only will it help you take care of your online travel agency, but it will also help you to cut some of the costs that you may have to encounter. You should also provide your customers with the option of giving in their recommendations or sharing their points of view. This way, you will know what your customers are looking forward to and it will also help you to come up with and generate some creative ideas to make the online version of your travel agency even more attractive. For example, you may get different ideas about the latest tourist attractions and different destinations or maybe the best hotels in different areas. It can also help you to understand the budget of your clients even better and how to accommodate them within their limited budget in a way that does not compromise on your profits.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">You must allocate a specific budget that needs to be used in your online travel agency. You can not keep your budget unlimited or make such a tight budget that it gets harder for you to develop your online travel agency. Hiring employees specifically for catering to the needs of your online travel agency can be a very intelligent way of making your life easier. In some areas, some legal formalities need to be fulfilled before you set up an online travel agency so, to avoid any possible constraints in the future, it is in the best interest of the organization to take care of those formalities in the very beginning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If all of these factors are taken into consideration, transferring your physical travel agency into an online one can be made very easy for you and running them both can not be very difficult after all.</span></p>\r\n', 'online travel agency, existing travel agency to online agency, online travel agency and physical agency, travel agency, ota ', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e4d30d1d1ee8.jpg', 1612, '2020-02-20 12:31:21'),
(99, 1, 'How to run parallel a physical and online travel agency.', 'how-to-run-parallel-a-physical-and-online-travel-agency', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">There are many multiple different travel agencies out there that have both, a physical working environment where the people hired at that particular travel agency work and an online version of the same travel agency as well that can be visited by multiple different people at different times from different parts of the world. Having a physical travel agency has both its advantages and disadvantages just like having an online travel agency would have. But the best way to weigh out the disadvantages of having a physical or an online travel agency would be to have both versions of your travel agency and operate them simultaneously operate them in different ways that are both effective and efficient.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">First and foremost, it is extremely important to make sure that the theme of your online travel agency and that of your physical travel agency are in alignment. Generally, people do not talk much about this but the minor details end up making a big difference at the end of the day, this is not only true for online and physical travel agencies but it is also true for any other organization that has a physical as well as a virtual platform where people can visit, interact, make payments, purchase different product or avail different services that are being offered to them. Having that said, minor things like the color scheme, font, type of content, number of options available for the customer, level of interactivity with the employee and modes of payment matter. All of these things should be the same throughout your brand, both in its physical self and its virtual self. For example, if the theme of your website is in the colors blue and white then the theme of your office should also be blue and white. Another example can be that if you only accept advance payments on your online travel agency then you should only accept advance payment system if a client visits you at your physical agency and inquires about different modes of payment.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Another thing that is extremely important to keep in mind is that whatever information that you are porting on your online website, it should be one hundred percent genuine and authentic. The main reason for that is because when a random person scrolling through the internet visits your website, there is a probability that that person can be your potential client from whom you can generate some business if not a great deal of it. So whatever impression your travel agency will make on that particular person will be through the online version of your travel agency so it is important to make sure that all the information that is being provided on your online travel agency in the original. It is also important to provide some background about your travel agency. The background can include things like how well established you are, when was your company founded, who is the founder of your company, the number of employees working at your travel agency, the services you provide, if your prices and packages are negotiable or not, the current market share that your company currently enjoys, what sets you apart or makes you unique as compared to the competing travel agencies, so on and so forth. The main reason for this is that the person gets the impression that you are a well-established brand and is inclined towards availing your service. This is important because if a client visits you in a physical environment, you will be able to provide him/her with all of that information but when you have an online version of your travel agency, this information must be conveyed to the person in one way or another.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Other than that, someone should always be there to answer any questions or queries that an online visitor might have. That is because when a client visits you personally to avail your service, you will be able to answer all of their questions there and then but if the same questions are not answered online then the person might feel that they should look for other online travel agencies who can help them out. Another key factor in successfully running parallel a physical travel agency and an online version of it is to invest an equal amount of time and money on both of it or prioritize one over the other based on its need. However, it is also important to keep in mind that the division of your time and money should be done in such a way that neither of them is neglected and both the versions of your travel agency help you generate more business and hence generate more revenues, eventually. It is also important to make sure that you are well aware of the firms that are competing against you, firms that are more successful than you and are trying to form a monopoly or firms that are just entering the market. That way you can come up with different strategies that can help your travel agency deal with that competition in both the online and the physical world.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To further make your life easier, you can install special software that can cater to the specific needs of your physical travel agency and the needs of the online version of your travel agency. This way, a lot of time and extra effort will be saved. Another thing that can be done is to hire more employees and make special teams for both the physical and the online travel agency so both of them get the appropriate amount of time and attention and keep on operating successfully.</span></p>\r\n', '', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e4bcb037efb4.jpg', 1312, '2020-02-19 12:31:45'),
(100, 1, 'How has technology helped travel agencies over the decades', 'how-has-technology-helped-travel-agencies-over-the-decades', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Technology has transformed all the aspects of our lives including the way we view different things. The large organizations and businesses and travel agencies have experienced a lot of growth and enjoyed a lot of popularity in the last few years thanks to all the technological advancements. Not only for the businesses that have already established themselves over the years, but the businesses and the organizations that are new in different markets also have a great advantage of existing in an era in which everything is technology dependent and everything can be done in a matter of a few clicks. Not only for the businesses, the speed, efficiency and the effectiveness of communications between the clients and the organization has created a lot of conveniences for the businesses as well as the clients. Because of the technology, the number of human errors has also substantially reduced increasing the quality of the service or a product being provided by a certain organization. Not only has technology helped other businesses but it has also helped the travel industries to completely change the landscape of the tourism industry and has helped them create a more customer-centric approach when conducting business, which has proved to be extremely beneficial. Because of the ease that has been resulted by the advancements in technology, the barriers to entry for new businesses and the different barriers of communication between those businesses and the clients are pretty much gone.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">One of the biggest advantages that we enjoy because of the technological advancements around us is the increased level of personalization in almost everything. With the latest technologies like cloud computing and big data around us, different travel agencies can add a very personalized touch to the way they operate thanks to these technologies. This also gives them an edge over other competing travel agencies in the market. Not only that, but it also helps the client to customize the service that they want to avail based on their likes and dislikes. This can also help the travel agencies to gather new ideas and be innovative in the way they conduct business. By doing this, not only is the client happy but it also helps the travel agency to gather all the additional information about their client that can help the travel agency to come up with a more suited package for their client along with many different offers in the future.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">People in today&#39;s day depend on reviews or what others think of a particular product or a service. The same is the case when people want to hire a travel agency to help them plan out a trip or a vacation for them. For example, a person might visit different travel blogs on Instagram, Facebook or Twitter to find out the latest tourist attractions and the places that people are visiting these days the most. They might also want to look up about the different hotels that they might want to stay in or the different hotels that they might want to try when they are on vacation. Not only the hotels and the restaurants but today&#39;s traveler will also look for the best airlines with nominal rates that are most suited to their budget and the best routes to their destination. Not only for the traveler himself, but the power of social media has also transformed the way travel agencies and other businesses operate. In today&#39;s world, it is extremely important to mark your presence in the online world through the different social media platforms that are available to us. Because of these social media platforms, travel agencies can make the online pages that help them to advertise their services to the people out there. These pages can also help them to get different reviews about how they are currently performing and what can be done to improve their services. Most importantly, these social media platforms are a great way to advertise your travel agency as there is an unlimited amount of viewership.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Another major advantage of technology that has been observed is the increased level of constant connectivity and mobility. These days people have their phone with them all the time, which means that they are constantly connected to the travel agency so that the traveler can keep the travel agency update about their requirements. This has also resulted in convenience and ease for the travel agency itself as it can also keep its clients constantly updated with the latest services and offers, moreover, if there is some sort of change in any one of the tours planned by that particular agency, the travel agency can instantly inform its client about that inconvenience and can provide it with other more suitable options for them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLooking to start your own travel portal?&nbsp;<br />\r\nCheck out our main site </span><a href=\"https://phptravels.com/\">https://phptravels.com/</a>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:11pt\">and let us help you to build your online travel portal&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', 'travel technology, travel agencies innovation, travel agencies decades', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e49aa35d4063.jpg', 1428, '2020-02-18 12:32:17'),
(101, 1, 'Different ways for travel agencies to improve their competitiveness in the market', 'different-ways-for-travel-agencies-to-improve-their-competitiveness-in-the-market', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">With the cut-throat competition in the market, it is extremely important to stay focused and come up with strategies that will not only help your travel agency to survive the rough competition that it might face but also help it to flourish. There are new travel agencies that are evolving day by day so it is extremely important that every step you take is extremely intelligent and helps your travel agency to beat the competition that it might face. With the large variety of travel agencies in the market, people have a wide variety to choose from. Your potential customer is not confined to use the services that are only provided by your travel agency, they can look around and pick whichever travel agency that they think is the best suited for their needs. This means that the customer has the negotiation power as whichever travel agency he or she picks would certainly not like to lose their customer to their competition. Travel agencies usually only focus on keeping their current clients happy and satisfied, hence loyal to them. However, in the process of doing that, they sometimes forget that other objectives need to be met as well, for example attracting new travelers. Having such a high level of competition in the market, it is extremely important to make sure that you make wise decisions that can only result in providing your travel agency an edge over its competition.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">One of the most effective technique that can be implemented to keep your customers loyal to your travel agency, increase the number of sales and revenues and build up a positive reputation for your travel agency can be highlighting the main benefits of availing the services being offered by your travel agency as compared to those that are being offered by your competitors. Instead of just focusing on beating up your competition, you can ask the satisfied customers to review your services that they once availed. This does not only help you in creating a positive image for your brand but it will also help you to attract more customers, as people tend to trust personal reviews more than actual advertisements from the brand itself. You can post those reviews on your official website for the public to view, this can also indirectly advertise your travel agency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Another important thing that can positively contribute to the success of your travel agency is the level of your interactions with your customers. A high level of interactions with your customers will portray a message on them that you are concerned about what you are providing them with. This will also help to get your customers to trust you with the decisions that you make for them. Not only that, as a travel agency you will also learn a lot more by being interactive with your customers, for example, their likes and likes, what their demand is or what they expect from you as a travel agency. You can use questionnaires, images, and videos to help you to be more interactive with your customers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Another thing that can help your travel agency to stand out in the market is to install the latest technology. This might mean that you have to install an online software that is best suited for your needs. Getting software for your travel agency may sound intimidating at first as they do tend to have a big price tag on them, however, if the returns on this investment are thought of in the long run then it is a smart thing to do. The software will not only make things faster in your travel agency, but it will also help you to store all the important data related to your customer that can be used later. Furthermore, depending on the type of software that you install, it can also help you with the bookings and the reservations. Having the latest technology within your organization can be of great advantage to you as a travel agency as everything at your organization is being done in a lot faster and efficient way.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Extending your B2B connections is another way of dealing with competition. Having good relationships with your partners means that they can help you to get into a new market and acquire new customers. This can also help you to learn a lot more about the demands of travelers and what they want along with what is new in the tourism industry.</span></p>\r\n', 'Different ways for travel agencies, different travel agencies, travel agencies, new travel agencies', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e44373da15ab.jpg', 1547, '2020-02-06 12:33:06'),
(102, 1, 'How to start OTA ( Online Travel Agency ) ', 'how-to-start-ota-online-travel-agency', '<p><br />\r\nExisting opportunities for creating a travel booking website<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Direct database is when you manually create your own travel database. This is usually done when the host is creating a website. For example, a hotel chain or a tour company that only wants to sell their own hotels or tours, or an airline that is selling their flight tickets direct to consumers. A direct booking portal can also be created if a company establishes contracts with host travel suppliers to manually list and upsell specific deals/products.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>01. Direct database</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/UXoW1BNqjenAQG-9jH0hEqTUb1thcgNU9Q68DUC3hJX5WJJ6NMiruYO3yjr8u27PFAjh-vkTjAsiE3YCqPBU9o5E8jqDUwdT5qZi8AYApmtFaFvdiyRMUXRqk8s4W75clrUYYnh8\" style=\"height:71px; width:298px\" /></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>02. GDS Integration</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/GrGUJts8Hrkbx1Lc0pzFr3HVDeMheJCXdGhX0kPNMhUt7lVg7d4eqLt9tU9SY9EWr66l6q8JSr9Eaf8pB8Bky-x96tsGsu5antRAXVm3FlVxfE_rTrXtkF_A2Bb9GYGE1y52YQS5\" style=\"height:72px; width:298px\" /></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>GDS integration is for OTAs (online travel agencies) to access full inventory of travel solutions to sell to their customers. GDS stands for the global distribution system that allows travel suppliers to distribute travel products, rates and relevant information for travel agents to sell. Some commonly known GDS providers are Amadeus, Sabre and Galileo, which is also known as TravelPort. GDS integration is only available for licensed travel agents that are ARC or BSP accredited. Once approved with the GDS, travel resellers have access to backend wholesale rates to buy services on customer&rsquo;s behalf. When an agent wants to showcase the GDS database on their website, API integration is done.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Affiliate integration is for start-up travel resellers who want to showcase a range of travel deals on their site to earn commission without having to be an agent. Affiliate is the easiest and most affordable solution, and is most often free to set up. Affiliate promoters share their booking commission with the affiliate company that is hosting the deals. It is a win-win partnership where the promoter gets access to promote travel services in return for shared commission. Affiliates often have creatives to promote such as text links, banner ads, widgets and white label search engines. The affiliates referral code is coded into the promotional creatives, so that when setup on a website, the affiliate earns a commission when their visitors are referred by them.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>03. Affiliate Integration</strong></p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/TqnEKZfDdoiI0W6lVYR9GilLO8Fko1bgxzy4LRO03nS5VWUNMJeSelgM4a01Ud7XpONZRSZX_hz0hSwolTdKPUw82PdgbYvDLoCXo8ReL2l3OfQngGQKMUw9p6quRgSMUxl0PJnP\" style=\"height:72px; width:298px\" /></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>04. API Integration</strong></p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/nI_0oH83wKb0wqcD2VhgOTFNzVVbhNsf23qmpXiosRZ9GhJ1U9VmW3Ye_U7UYyOb6DqvGTC5SVkgUMp8rUCR0opblSAYxeS9wQI-Keo_nYcJZgP3SE5mDI4_7IZ4EPM5dkhCIf65\" style=\"height:72px; width:298px\" /></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>API integration is more advanced than affiliate, because it takes more development time to setup and most travel companies do not allow their API to be used freely. A partner may need to be approved for API access before they can setup. The earning potential varies depending on which company&rsquo;s API you are setting up. Once approved, you will require an API developer to install the API, which can often require ongoing technical support. API stands for a set of functions or procedures allowing the creation of applications that access the features or data of an operating system, application or other service. When relating to travel development, APIs are used to showcase another travel company&rsquo;s inventory on your site, so that visitors can browse directly on the website and the deals can show in conjunction with other deals from other travel companies to create a comparison search engine. API is an advanced integration and is not a quick setup process. It requires a properly trained developer to assist with setup.&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">How data integration will work for your Travel website?<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe popularity of online travel agents(OTA) models grew in the Travel and accommodation field that led travel agents to use third party level APIs and integration for travel portals and online reservations. For your travel business, NCrypted Websites work on providing the two integration methods such as GDS and CRS.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhat is GDS?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Global distribution system (GDS) is an online system that utilizes a platform between tour operators and travel bookers by rendering streamlined services of hotel rooms, air ticketing, car rental, vacation rental and many more. GDS network helps travel agents and companies by balancing listings, reservation selections, rates, scheduling with the choice of permitting the customers to book tickets online.</span></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:14px\">GDS Integration<br />\r\nThe 4 leading GDS providers in the travel industry are given below.<br />\r\nAmadeus, Sabre, Galilio and Worldspan<br />\r\nThey are serving travel agents with quality service. At NCrypted, we have hands-on experience in integration of GDS and XML API to make your airline, hotel booking, car rental, vacation rental business fully automated and very easy</span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>What is CRS?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Computer reservation system (CRS) is the kernel of your hotel group procedures, centralizing the information from all your Property management systems (PMS) and other reservation systems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>CRS Integration</strong><br />\r\nWe integrate your CRS with some popular Online travel agents(OTA) as well as aggregators as mentioned below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MakeMyTrip, Expedia, Hotwire and CheapAir</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We provide service that integrates your CRS with major online travel agencies(OTA) to increase your reach globally and reduce the cost of your distribution.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Product Engineering - Travel Search</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Converting your Travel Search idea into execution demands domain understanding, proficiency, understanding and dedication. We offer custom product engineering solutions for your Travel Search Engine requirement. See how we can add value to your business to shape your idea into reality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Concepts</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We work on proof of concept(POC), minimum viable product (MVP), prototypes by assessing market size and segment, target audience, growth potential, etc. in order to validate your idea.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Analysis</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whatever is required to present and envision your Travel clone idea in order to implement, our Business Analyst team would be working on wireframes, SRS, SOW, diagrams etc. to analyze and present the vision.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Design</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will narrow down on the typical features required along with the UI and user experience that can engage your target audience. The Travel clone design could be identical to one of your reference Travel Search sites or it could be completely different and unique.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Development</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The development would be in accordance with your custom Travel clone requirements. We have Center of Excellence (CoE) assigned to carry out your requirements which involves agile development methodology and DevOps to implement the solution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Quality assurance</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure product efficiency, we carry out unit testing, integration and regression testing, which are complimentary for your assignment. On top of it we also provide speed testing, security testing, load testing, stress testing, server load balancing as per your requirement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Launch</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will help you with deployment assistance on your server to help you go live. You can host your Travel and Hotel Booking application with us as well. The server can be near to your location or the target market from where you are expecting the traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>We have the technology part covered for you</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Travel clone development is a complex process and comes with a lot of moving parts. Creating the digital infrastructure for Travel Search Engine development from scratch requires a longer turnaround time and hence becomes costly. We understand Travel Search development space and our clients benefit from our domain experience and robust backend technology.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>CUSTOMIZED TO SUIT YOUR BUSINESS MODEL</strong><br />\r\nWe know that a me-too Travel clone idea isn&#39;t enough to create a stir in the market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SCALABLE ARCHITECTURE</strong><br />\r\nScalable technology back-end for growing Travel Search demand - you will never have to redo it all over again!<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>GET READY TO HANDLE BIG DATA</strong><br />\r\nOperate big data in a timely manner with our high-powered analytics in a cost-effective manner.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>FAST TIME TO MARKET</strong><br />\r\nScalable architecture and our process-oriented rapid development approach ensure a quick go-to-market ETA!<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>COST EFFECTIVE</strong><br />\r\nPowerful technology back-end with basic ready-made modules save time and hence overall project cost for your Travel clone.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DOMAIN EXPERTISE</strong><br />\r\nOur unparalleled domain expertise in Travel Search Engine helps you to avoid common mistakes that other startups would do.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>What is the best solution?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best solution for your integration depends on your budget and the type of travel company you are creating.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAffiliate is the easiest and the lowest cost option. White label affiliate is very competitive,<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAPI is the best option for comparison sites, but requires approved access and a time consuming setup process with specialized developer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nGDS would be best for classical travel agents who are working offline and looking to access full inventory.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDirect booking is best for businesses that have already established their services and sell directly to consumers or resellers who are willing and able to create relationships and contracts to resell.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAre you ready to become the next million-dollar startup?<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are partnered with and helped 500+ startups and businesses, many of which are valued multi-million dollars today. Our primary focus would be on understanding your Travel business requirement and providing you with relevant technology solutions while keeping your target audience and market in mind. We understand that a serious Travel and Hotel Booking project is an on-going engagement that requires technical, functional, financial and emotional commitment. We want to believe in your idea as much as you do. Get in touch to find out how we can help and bring your Travel business idea to life so that you can go to market with confidence.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ideal travel booking website design concept&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/snrLJ7XQ6Mlvtv0uxR5OeDZmeXXhrxTUycdwZuCGWiYuV__raN-3UP_hZ4ztR3xbML6X7AEMWTuL5NRyofDdMSZHZ6btxTNpCDjkZYR_r0CM-s3P4OgPwAuihbMwHIj2n51BgQdB\" style=\"height:413px; width:624px\" /></p>\r\n', 'How to start OTA. start online travel agency, travel agency startup, startup ota ', 1, 6, 0, 'image_750x_5e4716051aa61.jpg', 3011, '2020-02-14 20:27:02'),
(103, 1, 'The present and future of travel agencies around the globe.', 'the-present-and-future-of-travel-agencies-around-the-globe', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The travel industry has seen many changes over the decades and even more, changes are expected to be seen in the coming future. Multiple different factors are contributing to this constantly changing world of the travel industry, for example, the increased levels of awareness amongst people and the technological advances being experienced. Not only the travel industry in different parts of the world has experienced a positive change, but they have also had to face many hurdles and difficulties because of the facilities being provided by Uber, Airbnb, Skyscanner, etc. These three platforms have completely transformed and dismantled the way we view traveling in general and have also disrupted some of the profound changes that were observed in the travel industries in previous years. The increased levels of demand for online travel agencies have been quite obvious over the years. Online travel agencies have completely taken over the tasks of booking tickets and making hotel reservations which were once the responsibilities of the virtual travel agencies. Yes, virtual travel industries are still there but the constantly growing market of online travel agencies is slowly and gradually taking over them.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">A very big part of the revenues and the profits that are being generated in the travel agency comes from the commissions that the travel agents earn through providing their services that are being demanded by the customers but the way those commissions are earned today has changed greatly if we compare it to the way they were earned, let us say, ten years ago. There was a phase in the 1990s when the travel agencies stopped paying commissions to their agents, back then a lot of extra services were started to be provided and a lot of value was also added in those services to earn more. Just like the 1990s, service providers like Uber and Airbnb have gradually started to take over the commissions being earned by the agents. Even though these service providers are gradually taking over the commissions being earned by private travel agents, this, however, is still not a very big problem. That is because along with the increase in the offerings of these service providers, travel agencies have also started coming up with different ways to up their game in the world of the travel industry for example by offering different types of holiday packages. The travel agencies have come up with different ways to keep u with the constantly growing markets however to secure a bright future, travel agencies must be innovative and are successful in capturing the attention of their target audience.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">One of the smartest ways to keep that captured interest within your organization is to add value to whatever you are offering to your client. The best way to add value to the services being provided by your organization is to focus on the tiny details, for example, the level of ease and comfort you can create for your clients when they are traveling. Things that can create ease and comfort for your client can include things like the type of hotels you get booked, the internet connectivity of that particular country, finding the appropriate traveling season for your client and currency exchange. Your client may not focus on these tiny details in the beginning but in case they end up facing any inconvenience in their trip, they might end up blaming you. That is why it is important to keep these things in mind, which will also help you to create more value for your services. Another way of adding value to your services can be to make useful recommendations to your client, for example, an attractive tourist destination that your client might be interested in.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">When we talk about the growth and the future of the world of travel industries, it can be said that the travel industry has the potential to do wonders in different areas of interest however those wonders are not being observed by the naked eye. A reason for that is that with the high levels of unpredictability, travel agencies prefer to keep things old fashioned and they prefer to keep functioning the way they have been. They are generally scared of taking new risks which results in them missing out on the opportunities as well. Another very important thing that should be kept in mind is the constantly increasing technological advances. Different travel agencies all over the globe have started using those technologies within their organizations and have started exploring new concepts. This has not only made the lives of the travel agents easier but also the lives of their respective clients as there are lesser complications involved and there is a lesser chance of things going wrong. If the travel agencies continue to make use of technology productively then it can confidently be said that the world of travel is bound to bloom in the future.</span></p>\r\n', 'future of travel agencies, travel agencies,  travel future, travel business', 1, 1, 0, 'image_750x_5f91754fc28d8.jpg', 797, '2020-10-22 16:26:35');
